Here's a simple HTML file that includes embedded CSS and JavaScript. This web app features a "gold hand wave cat" (often referred to as a "maneki-neko" or "beckoning cat") theme, reminiscent of a Chinese restaurant ambiance.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Gold Hand Wave Cat</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #d4af37; /* Gold color */
        }
        .cat {
            width: 200px;
            height: 200px;
            background-image: url('https://example.com/maneki-neko.png'); /* Replace with a valid image URL */
            background-size: cover;
            margin: 0 auto;
            animation: wave 1s infinite;
        }
        @keyframes wave {
            0%, 100% { transform: rotate(0deg); }
            50% { transform: rotate(15deg); }
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            background-color: #d4af37; /* Gold color */
            border: none;
            color: white;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #b5942a; /* Darker gold on hover */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to the Gold Hand Wave Cat Restaurant!</h1>
    <div class="cat"></div>
    <p>Click the button to receive good fortune!</p>
    <button onclick="showFortune()">Get Fortune</button>
    <p id="fortune" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold;"></p>

    <script>
        function showFortune() {
            const fortunes = [
                "You will find great success in your endeavors!",
                "A new opportunity is on the horizon.",
                "Good luck is coming your way!",
                "Happiness is just around the corner.",
                "You will meet someone special soon."
            ];
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * fortunes.length);
            document.getElementById('fortune').innerText = fortunes[randomIndex];
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions:
1. Replace the URL in the `background-image` property of the `.cat` class with a valid image URL of a maneki-neko (gold hand wave cat).
2. Save the code in a file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `cat-restaurant.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser to see the web app in action.
